name: Bristol's Rainshine, Millenium Part 1: Seagull at Pero's Bridge
description: Pero's bridge was completed in 1999, a Bascule bridge, its unique form is a part of the mechanism. The bridge is named for ‘Pero’ (1753-1789) an enslaved man who had been moved to Bristol in 1783. | 2592x3888px | f/8.0, 1/800s, 50mm | Canon 400D and Lightroom | Photographed 2nd June 2021 on a walk around the harbourside with Julia.
